        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 8:48PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 848 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alamogordo, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alamogordo, Tularosa, La Luz, and Alamorosa.

This includes Highway 54 in New Mexico between mile markers 70 and
78.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
